The template I provided earlier is for a single-column article. To convert it into a two-column format, you can make the following modifications:

- Add the `twocolumn` option to the document class line:
  ```latex
  \documentclass[12pt, a4paper, twocolumn]{article}
  ```

- Move the abstract before the `\maketitle` command to display it in a single-column format:
  ```latex
  \begin{abstract}
  Your abstract goes here. Summarize your research question, methods, main findings, and their implications in a concise manner.
  \end{abstract}
  ```

- To include an image, you can use the `graphicx` package and the `\includegraphics` command. Replace `image.png` with the path and filename of your image file:
  ```latex
  \usepackage{graphicx}
  ...
  \begin{figure}
  \centering
  \includegraphics[width=\linewidth]{image.png}
  \caption{Caption of the image.}
  \label{fig:image}
  \end{figure}
  ```

